  "instructions": [
    "Heat a deep frying pan to 350°F (175°C) with about 1/4 inch coconut oil at the bottom.",
    "Combine the gluten-free flour, almond flour, coconut flour, salt, and pepper in a large bowl.",
    "Add the egg, melted coconut oil, coconut vinegar, and diced tomato to the dry ingredients.",
    "Mix until a smooth batter is formed.",
    "Finely chop the onion and garlic and add them to the batter. Mix until well combined.",
    "Using a 1/4 cup measuring cup, scoop the batter into the hot oil.",
    "Fry the fritters until golden brown, about 2-3 minutes per side.",
    "Drain the fritters on a paper towel-lined plate.",
    "Serve warm and enjoy."
  ],
